rawHelp:
serened: serened -- SereneDB pg-wire server

Usage:
  serened <data-dir> [--flag=value ...]
  serened shell [duckdb-shell args ...]
  serened psql  [psql args ...]

Flag sources (absl built-in, full definitions under --helpfull):
  --flagfile=path1,path2     Read flags from one or more files (one
                             '--flag=value' per line, '#' comments OK).
  --fromenv=name1,name2      Read each listed flag from FLAGS_<name>;
                             missing env vars are an error.
  --tryfromenv=name1,name2   Same as --fromenv but silently skip
                             flags whose env var is unset.
  --undefok=name1,name2      Tolerate '--name1=...' even when no flag
                             with that name exists (useful for shared
                             flagfiles across binaries).

Help variants:
  --help                     This filtered banner.
  --helpfull                 Every absl-managed flag.
  --help=<substring>         Flags whose name or description matches.
  --helpshort                Project-defined flags only (no absl/gtest).
  --helppackage              Flags grouped by source-tree location.
  --version                  Print the build banner and exit.

  Flags from http:
    --http_compress_response_threshold (Response body size threshold for
      transparent gzip/deflate compression (0 disables compression).);
      default: 0;
    --http_keep_alive_timeout (Keep-alive timeout for HTTP and pg-wire
      connections (in seconds; 0 disables keep-alive).); default: 300;
    --http_return_queue_time_header (Return the x-serene-queue-time-seconds
      header on every response.); default: true;
    --http_trusted_origin (Trusted origin URLs for CORS requests with
      credentials.); default: ;

  Flags from log:
    --log_level (DuckDB minimum log severity at process start: trace | debug |
      info | warning | error | fatal. Override at runtime with `SET
      logging_level = '<value>'`.); default: "info";
    --log_storage (DuckDB log destination at process start: 'stdout' (default;
      container log drivers capture it), 'memory' (queryable via SELECT * FROM
      duckdb_logs()), or 'file://<path>'. Override at runtime with `SET
      logging_storage = '<value>'`.); default: "stdout";

  Flags from server:
    --server_compaction_threads (Threads in the iresearch compaction pool (0 =
      auto-derive from cores, clamped to [1, 4 * cores]).); default: 0;
    --server_cpu_threads (DuckDB executor pool size at process start. 0 = let
      DuckDB auto-detect from cpu_count. The SQL-level `SET threads = N`
      continues to win at runtime.); default: 0;
    --server_directory (Path to the database directory. Overrides any positional
      arg.); default: "";
    --server_endpoints (Endpoint(s) for client requests (e.g.
      `pgsql+tcp://127.0.0.1:7890`). Comma-separated for multiple. Supported
      schemes: pgsql+tcp, tcp, ssl, unix.); default: ;
    --server_io_threads (IO threads for HTTP and pg-wire connections (0 = max(1,
      cpu_count / 4)).); default: 0;
    --server_maximal_queue_size (Maximum FIFO queue depth per priority in the
      SchedulerFeature scheduler; controls backpressure for the HTTP/REST work
      queue.); default: 4096;
    --server_refresh_threads (Threads in the iresearch refresh pool (0 =
      auto-derive from cores, clamped to [1, 4 * cores]).); default: 0;
    --server_request_threads (Maximum worker threads for the SchedulerFeature
      pool (the legacy ArangoDB scheduler used for HTTP/REST work; distinct from
      server_io_threads and server_cpu_threads). 0 = auto-detect (max(32, 2 *
      cpu_count)).); default: 0;
    --server_skip_search_recovery (Skip the entire WAL replay phase for inverted
      indexes on startup. Diagnostic only -- data loss is permanent for the
      skipped delta.); default: false;

  Flags from ssl:
    --ssl_cafile (CA file used for client certificate verification. Empty
      disables client-cert checks.); default: "";
    --ssl_cipher_list (OpenSSL cipher list to restrict the server to. See
      OpenSSL docs.); default: "";
    --ssl_ecdh_curve (Colon-separated list of TLS key-exchange groups passed to
      SSL_CTX_set1_groups_list. Empty disables the call.);
      default: "x25519:prime256v1";
    --ssl_keyfile (Server private key (PEM, certificate + key concatenated).
      Required for SSL endpoints.); default: "";
    --ssl_prefer_http1_in_alpn (Prefer HTTP/1.1 over HTTP/2 in the ALPN
      selection callback.); default: false;
    --ssl_protocol (TLS protocol selector: 'tls' (generic, OpenSSL negotiates),
      'tls1.2', or 'tls1.3'. Legacy SSLv2/v3/TLSv1 are rejected.);
      default: "tls";
    --ssl_session_cache (Enable OpenSSL server-side session caching
      (SSL_SESS_CACHE_SERVER); off = SSL_SESS_CACHE_OFF.); default: false;

Try --helpfull to get a list of all flags or --help=substring shows help for
flags which include specified substring in either in the name, or description or
path.
